# Lambda deployment zip

When you change any file under `api/` (especially `api/index.js`), **always** create the Lambda deployment zip so the user can upload it without running the command themselves.

**Command** (run from repo root or from `api/`):

- **PowerShell:** From `api/` directory:
  `Set-Location api; Compress-Archive -Path index.js,bracket-regions.json,node_modules -DestinationPath ..\contest-api.zip -Force`
- Or from repo root:
  `Set-Location c:\Users\ryanp\Desktop\code\rp.com\api; Compress-Archive -Path index.js,bracket-regions.json,node_modules -DestinationPath ..\contest-api.zip -Force`

**Output:** `contest-api.zip` in the repo root (`rp.com/contest-api.zip`).

Run this at the end of your response whenever you have edited API code, and tell the user the zip is ready to upload to the Lambda console.
